---
import BlogPost from '../../../../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
import { BLOG_POSTS } from '../../../../data/blog';

const meta = BLOG_POSTS.find((p) => p.slug === 'place-first-non-qm-file-clout')!;

const faqs = [
  {
    question: 'How long does it take to get approved as a Clout wholesale partner?',
    answer:
      'Most brokers are approved and submitting their first file within 5 to 7 business days of sending the broker package. The package review takes 1 to 2 days; the AE onboarding call is 30 minutes; TPO Connect provisioning is same-day after approval.',
  },
  {
    question: 'What documents does Clout require for broker onboarding?',
    answer:
      'A standard wholesale package: completed broker application, signed broker agreement, W-9, current E&O insurance certificate ($1M minimum), company NMLS license, AML policy and procedures, and principal resumes. No background-check fees or upfront costs.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Can I run a scenario before becoming a partner?',
    answer:
      'Yes. Email PowerUp@CLOUTwmb.com or call 844-477-3111 with a high-level scenario — borrower profile, property, loan request, FICO band — and an AE will respond with whether it fits any of the 10 Clout programs. No NDA required for general eligibility questions.',
  },
];
---

<BlogPost
  slug={meta.slug}
  title={meta.title}
  description={meta.description}
  category={meta.category}
  datePublished={meta.datePublished}
  dateModified={meta.dateModified}
  lead="Placing your first Non-QM file with Clout follows the same six-step rhythm as every wholesale lender — but the conditions, scenario-desk usage, and AE handoff are what decide whether the file clears in 17 days or 47. This is the field guide we wish every new partner had."
  faqs={faqs}
>
  <h2>1. Run the scenario before you submit</h2>
  <p>
    The single most common reason a first file stalls is that the broker submitted before
    confirming program eligibility. Clout publishes a <a href="/tpo-connect/">scenario desk</a>
    that returns a same-business-day written eligibility opinion on clean scenarios received
    before 2 PM ET. Use it. Email the borrower profile, property, loan request, LTV, FICO band,
    and the specific question (will you approve, best program, max LTV) to your AE or to
    <strong>PowerUp@CLOUTwmb.com</strong>. The scenario response prevents 80% of
    decline-after-submission heartbreaks.
  </p>

  <h2>2. Pick the right program from the start</h2>
  <p>
    Clout has ten Non-QM programs. The right one depends on how the borrower's income is
    documented — not on what the borrower "wants." A few decision shortcuts:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Rental property, no W-2 income:</strong> <a href="/loan-options/dscr/">DSCR</a>.</li>
    <li><strong>Self-employed, business or personal deposits available:</strong> <a href="/loan-options/bank-statement/">Bank Statement</a>.</li>
    <li><strong>1099 contractor with strong gross 1099s:</strong> <a href="/loan-options/1099-only/">1099 Only</a>.</li>
    <li><strong>Non-US citizen, no SSN:</strong> <a href="/loan-options/foreign-national/">Foreign National</a>.</li>
    <li><strong>High-net-worth, thin documented income:</strong> <a href="/loan-options/asset-qualifier/">Asset Qualifier</a>.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    If the borrower fits more than one program, ask the AE which one the desk prefers for the
    specific FICO and LTV band — pricing and turn-times vary.
  </p>

  <h2>3. Register and submit through TPO Connect</h2>
  <p>
    All Non-QM files go through <a href="/tpo-connect/">Clout TPO Connect</a> (Encompass-powered).
    Upload: a completed 1003, tri-merge credit, income documentation per the program matrix,
    purchase contract or refinance worksheet, identification, and any LLC formation documents
    if vesting in entity. Clout does not accept paper, fax, or FTP submissions — only eDoc
    inside the portal.
  </p>

  <div class="callout">
    <p class="callout-title">Submission checklist</p>
    <p>
      1003 · tri-merge credit · 60 days bank statements · LOX for credit events · purchase
      contract or refi statement · LLC docs (if entity) · executed leases (if existing
      tenants) · prior year insurance binder · most recent property tax bill.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2>4. Expect an initial decision in 24–72 hours</h2>
  <p>
    Clout publishes a 24–72 hour initial-decision window across nearly all Non-QM programs.
    DSCR purchases tend to land in 24–48 hours; Foreign National and Asset Qualifier files
    take longer because of documentation seasoning and international credit translation. The
    AE will text or email you when the decision posts inside TPO Connect.
  </p>

  <h2>5. Clear conditions inside the 4-hour window</h2>
  <p>
    Conditions are where most files lose time — not because the lender is slow, but because
    brokers batch-respond to conditions a week later. Clout publishes a <strong>4-business-hour
    internal commitment</strong> on conditions review. If you reply to conditions the same day
    they post, the file moves at the pace the turn-time table suggests. If you batch them, it
    won't.
  </p>

  <h2>6. Get to clear-to-close inside the published window</h2>
  <p>
    Typical clear-to-close timelines, assuming a clean file and responsive borrower:
  </p>
  <div class="key-stats">
    <div><span class="k">DSCR purchase</span><span class="v">15–20 days</span></div>
    <div><span class="k">Bank Statement</span><span class="v">18–25 days</span></div>
    <div><span class="k">Foreign National</span><span class="v">25–35 days</span></div>
  </div>
  <p>
    After clear-to-close, the file moves to closing department for doc prep and TRID-compliant
    CD delivery. The borrower's 3-business-day TRID waiting period applies, then closing.
  </p>

  <h2>Frequently asked</h2>
  <div class="faq">
    {faqs.map((f) => (
      <details>
        <summary>{f.question}</summary>
        <div><p>{f.answer}</p></div>
      </details>
    ))}
  </div>

  <h2>Next steps</h2>
  <p>
    Not yet a partner? Start at the <a href="/tpo-connect/">TPO Connect partner hub</a> — the
    "Apply" section walks through the broker package and what happens in the first 7 days.
    Already onboarded? Open TPO Connect, run your scenario, and submit. The Clout
    <a href="/resources/glossary/">Non-QM glossary</a> covers the program-specific terminology if
    you want a quick refresher before the borrower call.
  </p>
</BlogPost>
